  "text": "5.1. Steinberg type module and induced modules. Let us recall the construction of some H Cl n -modules in [CITATION_1] . Fix a partition λ = (n 1 , n 2 , . . . , n r ) of n. Let S λ be the subgroup of S n generated by s i,i+1 for i = {1, . . . , n} \\ {n 1 , n 1 + n 2 , . . . , n 1 + . . . + n r }. It is easy to see that S λ is isomorphic to S n1 × . . . × S nr . Let H Cl λ be the subalgebra of H Cl n generated by all w ∈ S λ , x i (i = 1, . . . , n) and c i (i = 1, . . . , n). Let Seg λ be the subalgebra of H Cl λ generated by all w ∈ S λ and c i (i = 1, . . . , n).",
